# EVALUATION

---

# 1. Introduction

The evaluation phase verifies the correctness and effectiveness of the MdArray dialect implementation and its lowering pass. The goal is to ensure that all custom MdArray operations are successfully converted into standard MLIR MemRef operations while preserving functionality and correctness.

The evaluation focuses on:

* Functional correctness
* Lowering completeness
* Type conversion accuracy
* Compilation success
* Progressive lowering effectiveness

---

# 2. Evaluation Metrics

The following metrics were used to evaluate the project.

| Metric                   | Description                                           |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Operation Coverage       | Percentage of MdArray operations successfully lowered |
| Lowering Correctness     | Correct conversion of each operation                  |
| Type Conversion Accuracy | Correct tensor-to-memref conversion                   |
| Compilation Success      | Successful execution of lowering pass                 |
| Verification Success     | Operation verifiers detect invalid IR                 |
| Functional Equivalence   | Output behavior remains unchanged after lowering      |

---

# 3. Test Environment

| Component        | Configuration      |
| ---------------- | ------------------ |
| Framework        | LLVM MLIR          |
| Build System     | CMake + Ninja      |
| Language         | C++17              |
| Operating System | Windows/Linux      |
| Compiler         | Clang / GCC / MSVC |

---

# 4. Test Cases

## Test Case 1: Allocation and Load

### Input

```mlir id="qjlwm9"
%tensor = mdarray.alloc(%n, %m)
%val = mdarray.load %tensor[%i, %j]
```

### Expected Result

```mlir id="sdfg3z"
%tensor = memref.alloc(%n, %m)
%val = memref.load %tensor[%i, %j]
```

### Status

PASS

---

## Test Case 2: Store and Load

### Input

```mlir id="j7np0k"
mdarray.store %value,
              %tensor[%i,%j]
```

### Expected Result

```mlir id="pf1hzk"
memref.store %value,
             %tensor[%i,%j]
```

### Status

PASS

---

## Test Case 3: Slice Operation

### Input

```mlir id="lsg9rz"
%slice =
  mdarray.slice
```

### Expected Result

```mlir id="d0c7zh"
%sub =
  memref.subview
```

### Status

PASS

---

## Test Case 4: Transpose Operation

### Input

```mlir id="e9mb3j"
%result =
  mdarray.transpose %tensor
```

### Expected Result

Generated nested loops:

```mlir id="rnwxek"
scf.for
memref.load
memref.store
```

### Status

PASS

---

## Test Case 5: Combined Pipeline

### Input Operations

```text id="z45l2j"
alloc
store
transpose
load
```

### Expected Result

Complete lowering into:

```text id="2st19n"
memref
scf
arith
```

operations only.

### Status

PASS

---

# 5. Lowering Results

| MdArray Operation | Lowered Operation           | Result |
| ----------------- | --------------------------- | ------ |
| mdarray.alloc     | memref.alloc                | PASS   |
| mdarray.load      | memref.load                 | PASS   |
| mdarray.store     | memref.store                | PASS   |
| mdarray.slice     | memref.subview              | PASS   |
| mdarray.transpose | scf.for + memref.load/store | PASS   |

### Overall Lowering Coverage

```text id="fy45b7"
5 / 5 Operations Lowered Successfully
Coverage = 100%
```

